Element DataCollection
Namespace http://xml.insee.fr/schema/applis/pogues
Annotations
 
DataCollection : A data collection (or a data collection campaign) is a
survey data collection realization period. Each data collection can contain one ore several
questionnaire. It's characterised by a statistical operation and a period (M01 -
January,...,T02 - Second quarter,etc.). All these concepts are created outside Pogues.

Attributes
QName Type Use Annotation
agency xs:token optional 
Agency of Questionnaire. It's optional. Exemple :
"fr.insee".
depth xs:nonNegativeInteger optional
final xs:boolean optional 
final : boolean attrubute indicating if the questionnaire is final
or not
flowLogic FlowLogicEnum optional 
Survey designer should have the possibility to choose if they
prefer to describe the dynamic of their questionnaire (jump directly to a question,
a sequence or a subsequence according to a condition on some variables) with a GoTo
or an IfThenElse logic.
formulasLanguage FormulasLanguageEnum optional 
Choice of formula input language (VTL or XPATH). It applies to the
entire questionnaire, the mix of languages is not supported.
genericName xs:token optional
id xs:ID required

Element ComponentGroup
Namespace http://xml.insee.fr/schema/applis/pogues
Annotations
 
In some cases it make sense to have full components (e.g. components
imported from repository and not yet placed on the questionnaire), so to have both "Member"
(a list of members which could be empty) and "MemberReference" (a list of member
references).

  <Member id="">{0,unbounded}</Member>

</ComponentGroup>

    <xs:documentation>In some cases it make sense to have full components (e.g. components imported from repository and not yet placed on the questionnaire), so to have both "Member" (a list of members which could be empty) and "MemberReference" (a list of member references).</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
  <xs:complexType>

Element CodeType / Parent
Namespace http://xml.insee.fr/schema/applis/pogues
Annotations

Element NonResponseModalityType / Probe
Namespace http://xml.insee.fr/schema/applis/pogues
Annotations
 
NOT USED
 
Probing is a common technique that researchers use in
interviewer-administered surveys when respondents initially refuse to answer a question
or say they "don't know." Interviewers are trained to use neutral probing techniques --
such as "Would you lean more toward [answer] or [answer]?" or "Just your best guess is
fine" -- to encourage valid responses. Probing can be particularly effective when
respondents initially hesitate to provide an answer, and it can increase the number of
valid responses.

Simple Type QuestionTypeEnum
Namespace http://xml.insee.fr/schema/applis/pogues
Diagram
Type restriction of xs:token
Facets
enumeration SIMPLE 
a SIMPLE question is a question made of a label and only one response
domain whichever its type be: text, numeric, date, boolean, or less frequently any type
available in the DDI schemas.
enumeration SINGLE_CHOICE 
a SINGLE_CHOICE question is a question made of a label and a response
domain typed as a code list. This type of question allows to the respondent to select
one single response from a predefined list.
enumeration MULTIPLE_CHOICE 
A MULTIPLE_CHOICE question is a question whose label is the mutual part
of several sub-questions (constituting a coherent whole i.e an information axis). Each
modality of the information axis is peculiar to a specific response domain. This type of
question allows to the respondent to select the best possible answers out of a number of
choices from a predefined list.
enumeration TABLE 
A TABLE is a two-way table. It's a question made of a label and a
response domain defined by two dimensions. The information located at the intersection
of a row and a column corresponds to a response.
Used by

Attribute QuestionType / @questionType
Namespace No namespace
Type QuestionTypeEnum
Properties
content simple
Facets
enumeration SIMPLE 
a SIMPLE question is a question made of a label and only one response
domain whichever its type be: text, numeric, date, boolean, or less frequently any type
available in the DDI schemas.
enumeration SINGLE_CHOICE 
a SINGLE_CHOICE question is a question made of a label and a response
domain typed as a code list. This type of question allows to the respondent to select
one single response from a predefined list.
enumeration MULTIPLE_CHOICE 
A MULTIPLE_CHOICE question is a question whose label is the mutual part
of several sub-questions (constituting a coherent whole i.e an information axis). Each
modality of the information axis is peculiar to a specific response domain. This type of
question allows to the respondent to select the best possible answers out of a number of
choices from a predefined list.
enumeration TABLE 
A TABLE is a two-way table. It's a question made of a label and a
response domain defined by two dimensions. The information located at the intersection
of a row and a column corresponds to a response.
